Kano State government said preparations have reached an advance stage in organizing a stakeholder conference with a view of providing solutions to the menace of drug abuse, especially among the youth. Kano State Governor Abdullahi Umar Ganduje made this known during Iftar dinner hosted by the Emir of Kano Malam Muhammadu Sanusi II at the Emir’s palace onthe 28th day of Ramadan. This was contained in a statement issued yesterday by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor of Kano State Malam Abba Anwar. According to the statement, the emir had earlier recognised Ganduje’s effort in the fight against drug abuse among citizens and called for more concerted effort from stakeholders to get rid of the menace for a possible productive generation.